  <body>
    <p>This Conversion Instruction describes the conversion of CompositeCase 2.5 (PROD) schema in
      the document.</p>

    <p>The following criteria are used to identify composite cases: <ol>
        <li>The presence of at least 2 instances of this XPath:<ul>
            <li><sourcexml>/CASEDOC/case:body/case:headnote/case:info/case:courtinfo/case:courtname</sourcexml></li>
          </ul></li>
        <li>The presence of at least 2 instances of <i>either</i> of these XPaths: <ul>
            <li><sourcexml>/CASEDOC/case:body/case:headnote/case:info/case:courtinfo/case:dates/case:decisiondate</sourcexml></li>
            <li><sourcexml>/CASEDOC/case:body/case:content/case:judgments/case:dates/case:decisiondate</sourcexml></li>
          </ul></li>
      </ol>
    </p>
    <p><sourcexml>CASEDOC</sourcexml> becomes <targetxml>compcase:compositecourtcase</targetxml>.
      The attributes of <sourcexml>CASEDOC</sourcexml> are handled as follows: <ul>
        <li><sourcexml>@id</sourcexml> becomes <targetxml>@xml:id</targetxml>.</li>
        <li><sourcexml>@xml:lang</sourcexml> is suppressed (a separate rule has been defined to
          populate <targetxml>compcase:compositecourtcase/@xml:lang</targetxml>).</li>
        <li><sourcexml>@type</sourcexml> is suppressed.</li>
      </ul></p>
    <pre>

&lt;CASEDOC xml:lang="en-AU" ...&gt;
        ...
        &lt;docinfo:doc-lang lang="en"/&gt;
        &lt;docinfo:doc-country iso-cc="AU"/&gt;
        ...
&lt;/CASEDOC&gt;
<b>Becomes</b>

&lt;compcase:compositecourtcase xml:lang="en-AU"&gt;
      
      &lt;compcase:head&gt;...&lt;/compcase:head&gt;
      
      &lt;compcase:body&gt;...&lt;/compcase:body&gt;
      
      &lt;doc:metadata&gt;...&lt;/doc:metadata&gt;
      
&lt;/courtcase:courtcase&gt;
</pre>

    <p><targetxml>compcase:head</targetxml>, <targetxml>compcase:body</targetxml>, and
        <targetxml>doc:metadata</targetxml> are created as required children of
        <targetxml>compcase:compositecourtcase</targetxml></p>

    <note>The attribute <sourcexml>@searchtype</sourcexml> will be suppressed from the conversion
      except citation markup.</note>

    <section>
      <title>Note:</title>
      <p>Source elements and attributes are highlighted like this:
        <sourcexml>SOURCEXML</sourcexml></p>
      <p>Target elements and attributes are highlighted like this:
        <targetxml>TARGETXML</targetxml></p>
      <p>Copy source attributes to target attributes unless otherwise specified.</p>
      <p>Every example is represented like "EXAMPLE" in all the dita's and is captured
        under <pre>pre</pre> tag.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Changes</title>
